Raw: Preparations are now complete for the meeting of the Drummers ' Union in the Rehearsal Theatre to - morrow night , and a few tickets only remain to be sold . They can be had from Miss Janet MacLeod , 9 , Thornton Avenue , Streatham.

Preparations are going on apace for the Scottish Exhi- bition of the W.S.P.U. to be opened by Dr. Garrett Anderson late in April . At this exhibition the " Pageant of Great Women , " given in London by the Actresses ' Franchise League , will be repeated.
Details of a "Votes for Women " Parade , taking place in London to - day , will be found on p . 245

All those interested in the Women's Social and Political Union's General Election campaign will be glad to know that they will have an opportunity of hearing a number of Suff- rage speakers every Monday afternoon at the Queen's Hall , Langham Place, from 3 to 5
Next Monday afternoon the speakers will be Mrs. Pethick Law- rence and Miss Christabel Pankhurst , and Miss Decima Moore will recite " Woman This and Woman That . "
